  "prompt": "Do we have Financial Management in IPCC group 1 in may 2017? Websites show change in syllabus.",
  "response": "In May 2017, the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) implemented a new syllabus for the Intermediate level of the Chartered Accountancy course, affecting both IPCC and the revised Intermediate course. Under the old syllabus for IPCC (Integrated Professional Competence Course), Financial Management was part of Group 1; it was included within Paper 3, titled \"Cost Accounting and Financial Management.\"\n\nHowever, with the introduction of the revised syllabus in 2017, the structure and content of the exams changed. The revised Intermediate course included Financial Management as part of Paper 8, titled \"Financial Management & Economics for Finance,\" which is part of Group 2.\n\nIn summary, for May 2017 exams, if a student was still following the old IPCC syllabus, Financial Management was included in Group 1 as part of Paper 3. However, for students transitioning to the new syllabus effective from 2017 onward, Financial Management became part of Group 2. It\u2019s advisable to verify with official ICAI releases or direct communication from the institute for the most accurate guidance pertaining to specific sessions or personal study pathways.",
